# Doxygen-input documentation uses @ref cross-references whose targets contain
# underscores (e.g. `@ref DetWebServer::send_template`). Prettier parses those
# underscores as Markdown emphasis and rewrites them to `*`, which silently
# breaks the Doxygen links. These files are therefore excluded from Prettier;
# GitHub-facing Markdown (README.md, docs/CHANGELOG.md, …) is still formatted.
docs/README.md
docs/RFC.md
docs/SECURITY.md
docs/SSH.md
docs/TODO.md
test/README.md

# Generated data: the compiler dependency graph is written by tools/gen_dep_graph.py (compact
# json.dump) and regenerated verbatim by CI; Prettier would reformat it and cause churn.
test/dep_graph.json
# Likewise the SonarQube compile-commands baseline (tools/sonar/merge_compiledb.py json.dump,
# @ROOT@-tokenized); affected runs overlay it verbatim, so keep Prettier off it.
test/compile_commands.json
